com.delphix.masking.api.plugin.utils

Class SqlTypeMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.delphix.masking.api.plugin.utils.SqlTypeMapper

  • public class SqlTypeMapper
extends java.lang.Object
    This class maps text SQL types to data about those types. Information defining each known type and its metadata is stored in a CSV file. This information is specific to each database type, such as Oracle, MSSQL, etc.

    • Method Detail

      • mapTypeToMetadata

        public MaskValueMetadata mapTypeToMetadata(java.lang.String sqlType,
                                           int length)
        Return a MaskValueMetadata object with values appropriate for the SQL type passed. The inputs are a SQL type, which is just the base type - VARCHAR2 for instance, rather than VARCHAR2 (20 BYTE). The length input is what is stored in the length field for the data_column in MDS. The interpretation of this value depends on the datatype. It is usually byte or character length of the column, but for number types is sometime the bit precision of the field. For some types, it will always be zero as the type has fixed size.
        Parameters:
        sqlType - The SQL type
        length - The size of the column
        Returns:
        The metadata for sqlType, or null if the sqlType string didn't match any known type
